Reasoning: The paper discusses the analysis and optimization of dual-pivot quicksort algorithms, which are commonly used in computer science for sorting large datasets. This topic falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and algorithm analysis (cs.AL). The paper also includes discussions on information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) in the context of optimizing the algorithms. Additionally, the paper involves some aspects of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) in the modeling and analysis of the algorithms.
